Pirates have hijacked the Saudi-owned super tanker Sirius Star off the African coast, taking it towards a Somali port.
The US Navy is monitoring the situation, noting the pirates' ability to adapt tactics.
The fully-laden tanker was seized by armed men 420 nautical miles off Somalia.
The European Union launched a security operation to combat piracy.
NATO is considering long-term missions to counter piracy.
This hijacking, the largest and farthest out to sea, highlights the vulnerability of ships in the Indian Ocean.
Somali pirates have become more sophisticated, targeting larger vessels like oil tankers.
